[normal]WWC0026[bold]              [bold]                                              [bold]Written evidence submitted by [bold]NASUWT[bold] [bold]&#xa0;
[normal]The 
[normal]NASUWT
[normal]’s submission sets out the 
[normal]Union
[normal]’s views on the key issues identified by the Committee in the terms of reference for the Inquiry. The 
[normal]submission looks at definitions of the terms 
[normal]‘white’ and ‘working class’,
[normal] considers the reasons for the underachievement of white working
[normal]-
[normal]class children
[normal], outlines key things that 
[normal]the 
[normal]Government should be doing to address the issue and highlights some of the critical factors underpinning successful wo
[normal]rk in schools to improve educational outcomes for white working
[normal]-
[normal]class children.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The 
[normal]NASUWT
[normal] would be happy to give oral evidence to the Select Committee.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The 
[normal]NASUWT
[normal] is the largest teach
[normal]ers’
[normal] union representing teachers and school leaders in the 
[normal]UK
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
